You mentioned that the &quot;SS quests are apparently insanely hard, having to fight in a zone that is nothing but 60plus dragons to get the drops. &quot;<br>
<br>
I was under the impression that the Kael armor quest pieces also come from this same zone?  Fight in the Testing Halls of the TOV to get the SS quest drops and the fight in another area of the same zone to get the Kael drops.<br>
<br>
<br>
wouldn't both be &quot;insanely&quot; hard quest to complete?<br>
<br>
Question for all...<br>
If the Majority of the SGA is moveing in this progression of pickig up icewell drops, changeing faction and then picking up Thurg quest armors, then changeing again to get Kael quest armor, what happens to the group of people that are too low to participate right now?  Say in the future, if we were to follow this progression and were done raiding Kael for Thurg quests and starting the faction switch none of us would be able to help the next group of people that is just reaching the levels where they could be doing raids in Kael.  Will there be enough numbers in that level range to be able to do Kael raids?<br>
<br>
Here's my take as of now.<br>
I don't have much of a problem killing a few dwarfs for the RFV armor, it's some nice stuff.  I've got the gloves and the boots not sure if I'll be able to get anymore but that's ok with me, prior to the availability of the RFV warriors were often seen in thier early 50's with only crafted armor, I can live with that.  I do want to get as much of the Thurg quest armor as I can.  I'm a Dwarf and from a rp perspective (granted it got bent a little when I killed a couple dwarfs) I want to side with the Dwarves.  I don't feel the headache of all the faction switching is worth the rewards.  If I can manage to get all my thurg armor, then someday as I reach higher level will hope to get some SS armor and won't even worry myself over the Kael quest armor.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't mind seeing two factions in the SGA, and as those members who might be in there 30's or early 40's now, start reaching the level range where they can go after the stuff, the higher ups that have decided to align with the faction that member has chosen can freely help out without worrying about faction.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, I wish to help the SGA as best I can, if we decide as a whole to do the faction switching boogie then I'll go along for the ride.  Personally I think I'd like to be friends with the Dwarfs, and especially with the Dragons!<br>
<br>
<br>
Sorry for the length of this post... I think I had a lot of thoughts on this issue running around in my head for a very long time and they found a place to go finally =) <p><i><b><font color=red>
