<br>
Bottom line to all of this is play what ever faction you want. I seriously doubt any are going to push a certain faction on you or force you in a direction. This post was more in line with those of us that may be interested in playing all sides. Look at the recent Dragon Necropolis and WW groups, a few of the high levels that go to Kael regularly and get both COV and dwarf faction kill dragons now.<br>
<br>
Bar<br>
<br>
It's very possible to have great dragon and dwarf faction since killing a giant yields both. Actually if one started out just killing giants and then switched to dwarfs it is quite possible, although some what time consuming, that you could be both ally to the giants and the dragons. Killing dwarves does not affect COV faction at all.<br>
<br>
It's an interesting puzzel.<br>
